1
00:00:06,182 --> 00:00:09,812
They are called ‘the chit-jagat’ 
[and] ‘the achit-jagat’.

2
00:00:09,812 --> 00:00:12,088
Chit means the ‘spiritually 
conscious world’,

3
00:00:12,088 --> 00:00:15,414
achit means 
‘the unconscious world’.

4
00:00:15,634 --> 00:00:18,697
[Shadow Consciousness]

5
00:00:19,107 --> 00:00:22,597
Now, as a footnote, remember,

6
00:00:22,597 --> 00:00:27,058
everything is ultimately 
conscious substance.

7
00:00:27,059 --> 00:00:29,261
But, as Guru Maharāj says,

8
00:00:29,261 --> 00:00:33,259
“A part of the Perfect 
appears to be imperfect.”

9
00:00:33,259 --> 00:00:39,427
So, even this world:
the jīvas are sarva-gataḥ—

10
00:00:39,427 --> 00:00:41,030
they are everywhere.

11
00:00:41,030 --> 00:00:43,989
Meaning, if you really get into it,

12
00:00:43,989 --> 00:00:46,813
if you analyze this to the matter, 
to the nth degree,

13
00:00:46,813 --> 00:00:52,396
you’ll see, 
it’s a suspended animation

14
00:00:52,616 --> 00:00:57,678
of jīvas and conscious substance.

15
00:00:57,678 --> 00:01:02,055
So, we refer to it as achit— 
‘the non-conscious’, ‘unconscious world’,

16
00:01:02,055 --> 00:01:04,065
‘the material world’, ‘matter’.

17
00:01:04,065 --> 00:01:06,174
Because we are told, 
what is matter

18
00:01:06,174 --> 00:01:10,517
but like an iceberg floating 
in an ocean of consciousness.

19
00:01:10,517 --> 00:01:13,870
As Guru Maharāj says,
“The whole thing is hypnotism.”

20
00:01:13,870 --> 00:01:19,537
So, a cluster of subjective
concepts makes an object.

21
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:22,353
So, since it’s all consciousness,

22
00:01:22,353 --> 00:01:26,012
what Guru Maharāj 
is talking about here, saying ...

23
00:01:26,572 --> 00:01:29,243
Just like we see 
in this world, you know, we can see—

24
00:01:29,243 --> 00:01:36,393
the shadow of something 
is based upon the real thing.

25
00:01:36,543 --> 00:01:41,770
So it’s the ... He’s saying, 
for the chit, conscious subject,

26
00:01:41,770 --> 00:01:46,385
to experience the mundane, 
it can’t do it directly.

27
00:01:46,385 --> 00:01:47,709
So what does it have to do?

28
00:01:47,709 --> 00:01:53,755
You have to have a shadow representation
of the soul, of the conscious self.

29
00:01:53,755 --> 00:01:58,371
And that shadow can operate 
in the shadowy world.

30
00:01:58,371 --> 00:02:01,449
Оtherwise conscious cannot ...

31
00:02:01,449 --> 00:02:05,830
Consciousness cannot negotiate
the unconscious plane.

32
00:02:05,869 --> 00:02:09,827
So Guru Maharaj’s introduced 
the conception of chāyābhās, chidābhās—

33
00:02:09,827 --> 00:02:11,455
‘a shadow-self’.

34
00:02:11,455 --> 00:02:14,012
A shadow of mind is this mind,

35
00:02:14,012 --> 00:02:17,797
a shadow of the intelligence ...

36
00:02:17,797 --> 00:02:21,430
It’s a shadow-self operating 
in the shadow world.

37
00:02:21,430 --> 00:02:26,477
And we’re making so many observations
about shadow-like existence.

38
00:02:26,477 --> 00:02:27,693
That’s what it is.

39
00:02:27,693 --> 00:02:32,053
I mean, this is an involved subject,

40
00:02:32,053 --> 00:02:34,868
and we are at the last few minutes
of this talk.

41
00:02:34,868 --> 00:02:39,001
But that’s what he means: 
chit-jagat—‘the conscious world’,

42
00:02:39,001 --> 00:02:41,587
achit-jagat—‘the unconscious world’.

43
00:02:41,587 --> 00:02:47,507
So how can units of consciousness 
navigate the unconsciousness

44
00:02:47,507 --> 00:02:50,584
or perсieve and deal 
with the unconscious?

45
00:02:50,584 --> 00:02:57,064
So, he has introduced the conception: 
chidābhās, ‘a semblance’,

46
00:02:57,064 --> 00:03:01,007
chāyābhās—‘a shadow self’

47
00:03:01,007 --> 00:03:03,612
can operate, can deal with that.

48
00:03:03,612 --> 00:03:06,913
That’s what it means.

49
00:03:08,283 --> 00:03:11,053
But ultimately all of this
[knocks on the seat]

50
00:03:11,053 --> 00:03:13,868
he said, 
“The world is in the mind”—

51
00:03:13,868 --> 00:03:16,009
Bishop Berkeley.

52
00:03:16,729 --> 00:03:18,395
And the parody, 
comedian goes,

53
00:03:18,395 --> 00:03:22,809
“Oh, you mean, none of this exists, 
we just think it does?”

54
00:03:22,809 --> 00:03:25,472
That’s not what he’s saying.

55
00:03:25,472 --> 00:03:29,814
He’s saying, “All of this
that we perceive,

56
00:03:29,814 --> 00:03:32,233
is floating in consciousness.”

57
00:03:32,233 --> 00:03:33,543
That’s what he means to say.

58
00:03:33,543 --> 00:03:37,911
“The world is in the mind, 
and not the mind is in the world.”

59
00:03:37,911 --> 00:03:45,510
So, you know, these are 
deeply philosophical questions

60
00:03:45,909 --> 00:03:48,589
and important, nonetheless.

61
00:03:48,589 --> 00:03:50,983
But we’re told, 
in the Bhagavatam, the example,

62
00:03:50,983 --> 00:03:53,550
and we can see now 
in the rainy season:

63
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:56,800
the cloud is covering the moon,

64
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:59,455
but the moon is illuminating 
the cloud.

65
00:03:59,455 --> 00:04:02,155
So all you see is the cloud,

66
00:04:02,155 --> 00:04:05,438
but without the illumination 
of the moon

67
00:04:05,438 --> 00:04:07,908
you’d see nothing.

68
00:04:07,908 --> 00:04:14,788
So don’t think the cloud, 
the illumined cloud is the real thing—

69
00:04:14,788 --> 00:04:17,362
it’s the moon that’s covered 
by the cloud.

70
00:04:17,362 --> 00:04:19,018
So what it means to say is

71
00:04:19,018 --> 00:04:27,648
“The soul is covered by the body, 
mind, senses, ego

72
00:04:27,648 --> 00:04:30,137
and is illuminating them.”

73
00:04:30,137 --> 00:04:33,143
So what we see— 
the radiance of a person,

74
00:04:33,143 --> 00:04:37,823
the look in their eyes, 
the signals, signs

75
00:04:37,823 --> 00:04:41,318
that tell us of the presence 
of a person—

76
00:04:41,318 --> 00:04:44,015
really the soul 
is in the background

77
00:04:44,015 --> 00:04:47,045
and that’s our interest.

78
00:04:48,425 --> 00:04:49,965
Hare Kṛṣṇa!

